Reasoning: The paper discusses algorithmic questions related to the colorful Carath\'eodory theorem, which is a geometric result with connections to combinatorial optimization and linear programming. The paper also discusses a reduction from computing a Nash equilibrium in a bimatrix game to a colorful linear programming problem. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry). Other likely sub-categories include cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
